Description: Kodiak Data is an edge-cloud solution provider enabling customers to easily deploy and scale big data infrastructure in both private.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Kodiak Data is serving a market need that has emerged at the confluence of three shifts in the industry: growing adoption of Big Data, shift to private and public cloud, and containerization. Big data workloads and clustered workloads have different requirements than do web and machine-to-human workloads and, thus, are served neither efficiently nor scalably by existing cloud solutions. Kodiak Data has developed an edge cloud solution that solves the infrastructure demand for Big Data. The product fits seamlessly between the user, and their public cloud or on-prem infrastructure, and requires no major implementation on the end of their customers. Since deploying the solution with revenue generating customers in Q4 2016, Kodiak Data has seen 5X lifts in speed and dramatic cost savings in customer case studies. At its core, Kodiak Data is a software company that containerizes clusters for big data developers and IT. The team has deep technical expertise in networking, virtualization and storage, and is supported by advisors and investors who are leaders in the database, virtualization and networking industries. Institutional investors include Data Collective (DCVC), Divergent Ventures, and Aspect Ventures.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Software

Industries: Cannabis, Law Enforcement, Life Science, Neuroscience
Description: IMMAD is a company that specializes in the responsible use of marijuana.  IMMAD technology is a tool for law enforcement use roadside.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Impairment Measurement Marijuana and Driving (IMMAD) is a test of visual impairment using a tablet or cell phone screen to quickly test the central forty degrees of visual field.   There already are standards in many driving related regulations for size and function of visual field and peripheral vision.  IMMAD tests central vision.  IMMAD uses striped square or circle targets that are five degrees.  The stripes may appear anywhere within the central forty degrees of vision and are of varying contrast.  With marijuana use a person cannot see the stripes that are of lower contrast. The signal used in IMMAD has been demonstrated to be extremely sensitive in the detection of marijuana related driving impairment in preliminary testing.  IMMAD will be a simple two- minute objective test in a tablet or cell phone.  IMMAD uses proprietary technology to measure the sensory functional visual deficits caused by marijuana use.  It capitalizes on the retinal dopamine depletion and acetylcholine neurotransmitter inhibition that occurs with marijuana use.  Acute and chronic use of marijuana impairs retinal ganglion cell functioning.  Functional impairments measured with IMMAD correlate with blood biomarker measures of tetrahydrocannabinol (THC).
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Community and Lifestyle, Food and Beverage, Government and Military, Health Care, Privacy and Security, Science and Engineering
